        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 10:40PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 1039 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Castlewood, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clear Lake, Castlewood, Claremont Colony, Bemis, and Poinsett Colony.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
